  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study aims to assess the agreement between respiratory mechanics parameters measured
      noninvasively by means of brief airways occlusions at the beginning of inspiration and the
      reference parameters obtained with standard techniques of esophageal and gastric pressure
      under static and dynamic conditions in a mixed population of ICU patients mechanically
      ventilated in pressure support ventilation mode.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
